  "title": "An Endangered Devil Named Mary Escaped. For 15 Days.",
  "script": "An endangered devil went missing! Mary — a 2-year-old Tasmanian devil at Paradise Country wildlife park on the Queensland Gold Coast — slipped out of her enclosure on June 2. Keepers had no idea how. They theorized she made an abnormally large leap. A thermal-imaging drone swept the bush for 3 straight nights. A sniffer dog joined the search. Wildlife experts combed the area. Nothing. For 15 days, Mary was gone. Then they found her — less than 2 kilometres from the park, but in critical condition. After 15 days in the wild, this shy, endangered marsupial needed emergency veterinary care to stabilize her. She survived. Mary is now at a specialist hospital recovering. So: how does a scared Tasmanian devil hide from a thermal drone for 2 weeks?",
